{"id":"fact-example-001","type":"code_quirk","fact":"Example: The UserService caches results for 5 minutes, so updates may not appear immediately in queries.","recommendation":"Use cache invalidation after writes, or query with { fresh: true } option.","confidence":"medium","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"discovered during debugging","date":"2026-01-15"}],"tags":["caching","user-service"],"affectedFiles":["src/lib/services/user.service.ts"],"affectedServices":["UserService"],"createdAt":"2026-01-15T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-15T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"fact-post-with-revision-shape","type":"code_quirk","fact":"PostWithRevision extends Post with revisions: PostRevision[] array, NOT flat content/revisionNumber fields. Latest content is accessed via currentPost.revisions[0]?.content.","recommendation":"When displaying post content, always access through the revisions array. Use optional chaining since revisions could be empty.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #16 implementation","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["types","posts","revisions","shared-package"],"affectedFiles":["packages/shared/src/types/post.ts","packages/client/src/**/*.vue"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"fact-migration-001-search-infrastructure","type":"code_quirk","fact":"packages/server/src/db/migrations/001_initial-schema.sql already ships the complete search infrastructure: pg_trgm + unaccent extensions (lines 4-5), forge_search text-search configuration with english_stem + unaccent (lines 7-9), posts.search_vector tsvector column (line 35), GIN indexes on search_vector and title trgm (lines 121-122), the update_search_vector trigger weighting title A / latest-revision content B / tag names C (lines 129-157), and refresh triggers on post_revisions and post_tags (lines 238-259).","recommendation":"Any future work on search features — filtering, ranking, autocomplete — should verify this existing infrastructure rather than re-create it. A new migration is only needed when *extending* the vector (e.g., adding comment bodies to the mix). For a new search endpoint, use plainto_tsquery('forge_search', $1) and ts_rank(search_vector, query) without any additional DB setup.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #3 search implementation","date":"2026-04-13"}],"tags":["postgresql","search","migrations","tsvector","pg_trgm","pre-existing"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/db/migrations/001_initial-schema.sql","packages/server/src/db/queries/search.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
